µC5Ghandy:µC4Do you want to tell us any last words?
 
µC5Mel'o Dee:µC4 If you want to live from your music you have to work hard. You have to be flexible and open and strong minded. Your relation to your hobby music becomes mixed up and the "flow"-feeling changes. In the beginning you won't compose as much as you did before because you have to organize yourself, your network and all the financial relations. Everyday you are the only one who motivates yourself. You have to pay somthing like a personal price to establish creativity in your life. This is and will be a continuous personal challenge that's worth living. But don't forget to become something like a businessman too. And if you don't live in the neighbourhood of those working creatives, connect and meet them, talk to them. Don't give up to follow your dreams.
 
If you are creative become aware of your abilities and believe in yourself. Strengthen your conciousness and maybe you learn that you can go your indivdual way. It's not so important to become a wellknown great creative person. It's better to live a creative and fullfilled life. To understand more of yourself and these whishes I admire you to read the following books from Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi Creativity, flow, finding flow - all available at amazon.com or amazon.de!
 
Best regards and many thanks for the interview, Heiko Klueh.
